post_text:
Hello Seekonk Public Schools Families,
Bus registration for Seekonk Public Schools is set to close on July 31st. Due to the uncertainties presented in this school year's startup there will be no extensions on that deadline, with any registrations received after that point placed on a waitlist. Our goal is to provide transportation services to every family that needs it. To do this all families in need of transportation will need to have their bus registration submitted by July 31st. If you have already submitted a registration, we thank you and no further action is needed at this time. A bus registration is attached to this email and a link to register online is included here: https://forms.gle/Bo5r3CgybiiNsyMd7. Either method is acceptable and bus fees have been waived for this school year.
Thank you and stay safe.

post_text: The School Committee held a regular meeting on Monday, April 13, 2020. This was the second virtual meeting. The meeting was scheduled to begin at 7:00 P.M. Per Governor Baker's Order suspending certain provisions of the Open Meeting Law, G.L. c. 30A, sec. 20 the public was not permitted to physically access this School Committee meeting and therefore, the meeting was held VIRTUALLY.

post_text: Families we are here for you! Starting Monday, April 6th we will be offering a Virtual Parent Tech Night at 7:00pm to answer your technology questions to help support your child during distance learning! We hope you will join Colleen Terrill, Director of Technology and Digital Learning, Suzanne Larson, SHS Library Media Specialist, Jenn St. Michel, HMS Library Media Specialist, Mindy Andrews, Martin Elementary Library Media Specialist, Audrey Lamar, Aitken Elementary Library Media Specialist and Beth Haselton Elementary Technology teacher. Each evening, April 6th to the 9th will focus on a different school! Please see your email for further details or email terrillc@seekonkschools.org.
